commit.message: Enumerate all control pictures in the comment.
An empty line for readability.
Macroize returning an option error.

Add comments showing replacement symbols.

The text being converted might be in an ancient encoding, thus we can't use
Unicode yet, and HTML escapes are hard to read.

ansi2*: recognize and ignore attempts to set G0/G1 charset

We might actually implement these charsets some day, but nah...
PuTTY's reluctance to heed them in UTF-8 mode has eliminated any use
in still maintained software, making this a very low priority task.

Drop invalid signatures for main().

It's the only case where K&R-style empty parameter list makes sense.

Bump CMake version.

The new syntax allows specifying a preferred version rather than just
the worst required baseline.

Also, versions <3.1 are no longer relevant, thus we can drop compat.
